Uses of Package
music

  • Packages that use music 
    Package Description
    grammar
    Package containing all of our grammar files.
    music
    Contains all of the datatypes responsible for containing musical elements.
    player  
    tests
    Package containing all of our test files.
  • Classes in music used by grammar 
    Class and Description
    ChordSequence
    The Interface ChordSequence represents any contiguous block of music from a single voice, including lyrics (because Chords contain their associated syllables) Immutable because it's an interface.
    Fraction
    The Fraction class is a mathematical fraction with a numerator and denominator.
    KeySignature
    The Class KeySignature represents a key signature for a measure.
    Note
    The class Note represents a note and contains its pitch, duration and accidentals.
    Song
    A Song represents an entire, playable musical piece.
  • Classes in music used by music 
    Class and Description
    Accidental
    The class Accidental represents an accidental for a given note.
    AccidentalType
    The Enum AccidentalType represents the possibilities for Accidentals.
    Chord
    The Chord class represents a single note, a chord, or a rest.
    ChordSequence
    The Interface ChordSequence represents any contiguous block of music from a single voice, including lyrics (because Chords contain their associated syllables) Immutable because it's an interface.
    Fraction
    The Fraction class is a mathematical fraction with a numerator and denominator.
    KeySignature
    The Class KeySignature represents a key signature for a measure.
    KeyType
    The Enum KeyType represents a variety of possible key signatures.
    Note
    The class Note represents a note and contains its pitch, duration and accidentals.
    ReadyToAddItem
    The Interface ReadyToAddItem represents a note or lyric that is ready to add to a SequencePlayer.
    Syllable
    The class Syllable represents a single syllable of the lyrics.
    Tuplet.TupletType
    The Enum TupletType.
    Voice
    The class Voice represents a voice (this is the highest level of ChordSequence).
